"Camp C.D., Tung K.K.","Surface warming by the solar cycle as revealed by the composite mean difference projection",2007,"Geophysical Research Letters","34","14", L14703,"","",,,10.1029/2007GL030207,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34548598654&partnerID=40&md5=e5caebdf22d1d99a0d9ec28fe2477289","Department of Applied Mathematics, University of Washington, Seattle, WA 98195, United States","Camp, C.D., Department of Applied Mathematics, University of Washington, Seattle, WA 98195, United States; Tung, K.K., Department of Applied Mathematics, University of Washington, Seattle, WA 98195, United States","By projecting surface temperature data (1959-2004) onto the spatial structure obtained objectively from the composite mean difference between solar max and solar min years, we obtain a global warming signal of almost 0.2°K attributable to the 11-year solar cycle. The statistical significance of such a globally coherent solar response at the surface is established for the first time. Copyright 2007 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Atmospheric temperature; Signal processing; Solar energy; Solar wind; Statistical methods; Composite mean difference projection; Solar cycle; Solar response; Surface temperature; Surface warming; Global warming; climate change; global warming; solar cycle; surface temperature",,,,,,"Cai, M., Dynamical amplification of polar warming (2005) Geophys. Res. Lett, 32, pp. L22710. , doi:10.1029/2005GL024481; Camp, C.D., Tung, K.K., The influence of the solar cycle and QBO on the late winter stratospheric polar vortex (2007) J. Atmos. Sci, 64, pp. 1267-1283; Camp, C.D., Tung, K.-K., Stratospheric polar warming by ENSO in winter: A statistical study (2007) Geophys. Res. Lett, 34, pp. L04809. , doi:10.1029/2006GL028521; Clements, A.C., An ocean dynamical thermostat (1996) J. Clim, 9, pp. 2190-2196; Coughlin, K., Tung, K.K., Eleven-year solar cycle signal throughout the lower atmosphere (2004) J. Geophys. Res, 109, pp. D21105. , doi